RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RANCHO RED was allowed to settle in the early going, improved position while outside of rivals on the turn, mounted a four wide bid into the stretch, came within aim of GRIFFITH PARK in mid-stretch, made a steady gain on that rival inside of the furlong marker, drew to even terms at the sixteenth-marker and wore down the runner-up in the final stages to prevail. GRIFFITH PARK contested the early pace with several rivals then assumed command heading to the turn, drew to a clear lead nearing the quarter marker, kept to task in the drive while staying clear to the furlong pole, was confronted nearing the sixteenth-marker by RANCHO RED, met that bid to deep stretch but could not hold off the winner in the final stages and bested the rest. THECHIEFHASTRICKS was away a bit slowly in the early going and was unhurried to the turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, swung four wide into the stretch, closed in the final furlong and was up for the show in the final strides. REALLY EASY contested the moderate early pace, chased GRIFFITH PARK along the turn, lost position approaching mid-stretch, faded in the late stages and was just edged for the show. FINE SOFT MORNING disputed the early pace then took back to stalk the moderate fractions, raced three wide along the turn, ran evenly to the furlong grounds and weakened in the late stages. LET GEORGE DO IT contested the early pace then took back to chase into the turn while between rivals, chased from the rail to the quarter marker, dropped back leaving the turn and tired in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 72. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MATCHLESS stalked the moderate early fractions, advanced while two wide on the turn, mounted a three wide bid into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, responded to steady urging in the final furlong, confronted SHE'S SO FANCY nearing the sixteenth-marker, matched strides with that rival to deep stretch and bested the game runner-up on the wire to prevail. SHE'S SO FANCY broke alertly, pressed the moderate early pace while on a hold, dueled with DANZIGS STAR STORM to the quarter marker, battled with that rival to mid-stretch, took a narrow lead nearing the furlong pole, was confronted by MATCHLESS nearing the sixteenth-marker, met that bid to the finish and was gamely bested for the win, while holding safely for the place. DANZIGS STAR STORM was sent to contest the early pace, set pressured fractions to the quarter marker, battled with SHE'S SO FANCY to mid-stretch, lost the lead to that rival nearing the furlong grounds, stayed on in deep stretch but was outfinished by the top pair and held safely for third. LOVE LOST chased the moderate early pace from the inside, shifted out in upper stretch and lacked a late response.

CANDY'S CLONE was prominent in the early stages, pressed the decent pace to the quarter marker, took a narrow lead nearing the furlong marker, battled gamely in deep stretch while running on the left lead, was outfinished in the final strides for the win by TAMANTARI and just held for the place. OLIVIA'S CHOICE (IRE) hopped at the start and was off slowly, chased the decent early fractions, raced two wide into the turn then was roused three wide into the stretch, came within aim at mid-stretch, was gaining in the late stages and just missed for the win and place, while well clear for the show. TAMARA MINE stalked the decent early pace from the inside, came in tight approaching the turn, took up at the three-furlong marker, dropped back and was unable to muster a late response. LA PRIMER ESTRELLA was hard to load, showed early speed and set a pressured pace to the turn, set decent fractions to the quarter marker, could not keep pace in upper stretch and tired in the late stages.

UPDRAFT broke alertly and was sent to establish the early lead, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, was confronted nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, chased to the eighth pole and gave way in the final stages. WOLF'S LIFE was allowed to settle while not far back, came in a bit tight entering the second turn, dropped back in upper stretch and did not rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1 1/4M All Weather Track CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Weight, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since January 1 Al lowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered for the Optional Claiming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIO KING unhurried early and content to trail the field through the early stages, was still last going into the far turn, was asked for more run with three furlongs to go and responded with sweeping move around the field, came into the stretch five-wide and ran away from the rest under a brisk hand ride while on the wrong lead. SECRET CLUB was not asked for speed from the gate, was caught three wide into the first turn, bid four wide in the sprint for the wire, could not keep pace with RIO KING in deep stretch and won the nod for second in the final strides. BIG FLAME held up near the rear of the field while saving ground, moved up into contention going into the far turn, was stuck behind horses for the whole of the turn and into the stretch, got some room near the eighth pole, finished evenly in deep stretch and was just edged for the place, while holding for show. ACCLIDER was content to track LIL MIRACLE MAN from a length or two behind to the far turn, moved to challenge from the five-sixteenths pole, may have gained a brief lead at the top of the stretch, ran on well but was outfinished in the final yards for a minor award. GALLANT WARREN held up in mid-pack through the first half-mile, pulled closer to the leaders down the backstretch, bid for the lead with three furlongs to run, was between horses in the sprint for home but was outfinished in the late stages. OTTAWA FIRE (IRE) away well then forced to check sharply when LIL MIRACLE MAN took the path passing the five-sixteenths pole, regained his stride and relaxed nicely in a tracking position while saving ground, checked again going into the far turn while boxed in on the rail, had to wait for racing room while full of run through the turn, held position while still behind horses to mid-stretch then checked again when ACCLIDER came over in the final yards. LIL MIRACLE MAN came away from the gate intent on getting the early lead, crowded OTTAWA FIRE near the rail passing the three-sixteenths pole for the first time, was allowed to set leisurely fractions while leading a parade of horses to the far turn, quickened when the race turned into a sprint past the five-sixteenths pole, held on to mid-stretch then weakened in the last furlong.
